  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Your people have extraordinary luck, which you have learned to lend to your companions when you see them falter. You're not sure how you do it; you just wish it, and it happens. Surely a sign of fortune's favor!</p>\n<p>When an ally you can see within 30 feet of you rolls a 1 on the [[/r d20]] for an attack roll, an ability check, or a saving throw, you can use your reaction and expend 1 luck point to let the ally reroll the die. The ally must use the new roll. When you use this ability, you can't use luck points before the end of your next turn. </p>",
